metadata.dc:description: Jejunal leiomyosarcoma, is an uncommon neoplasm. Diagnosis can be difficult because symptoms may be vague and nonspecific. We report the case of a 33-years-old patient, which was diagnosed and operated of this infrequent pathology.
metadata.dc:title: Leiomiosarcoma de yeyuno. Presentación de un caso.
[Jejunal leiomyosarcoma. A case report].
